I"ï<p>Phenomenal representations are a special type of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/mental-representations-connect-internal-with-external-state">mental representations</a>. Whereas <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/mental-representations-connect-internal-with-external-state">mental representations</a> are merely <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/tools-for-thought-interface-users-with-knowledge">tools</a>, phenomenal representation is self-conscious usage of those tools, avoiding homoncular explanations by pointing to a model of self-consciousness. <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/qualia-provide-experiential-knowledge">The wavelength of red would be a mental representation, while experiencing redness would be a phenomenal representation</a>. In <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/conscious-unconscious-divide-has-edge-cases">blindsight</a>, some <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/mental-representations-connect-internal-with-external-state">mental representations</a> can‚Äôt turn into phenomenal ones. Representations of the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/virtual-reality-renders-abstract-concepts-into-tangible-objects">actual</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/physical-telepresence-enables-shared-tangible-manipulation">concrete</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/attention-distorts-time">‚Äúnow‚Äù</a> are simply presentations. <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/experience-sampling-faces-an-accuracy-attrition-trade-off">Experience</a> is a trajectory through <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/phenomenal-space-is-adaptive">phenomenal space</a>.</p>
